==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Sanskrit]] [[Kamboja]]

===Pronunciation===
*kum'boj'ka

===Noun===
'''Kambojaka''' (''plural:'' Kambojakas)
# Another name for Sanskrit Kamboja (found in ancient [[Pali]] texts).
# Name of female sculpture  at [[Mathura]] [[Museum]], said of [[princess]] Ayasi Kamuiá  (Kambojaka), the chief [[queen]] of [[Saka]] Mahakshatrapa [[Rajuvula]]. Princess Aiyasi is stated to be grand niece of king Maues or Moga, the ancient ruler of [[Gandhara]].

===Alternative spellings===
*Kambo]ika

===Adjective===
<!-- this may be another case of a noun used adjectivally. -->
'''Kambojaka''' (''no {{compar}} or {{superl}}'')
# Devoted or loyal to Kamboja. 
# Relating to the Kambojas.

See [[Kamboja]]

